11.28.24  9:43 am   The text in your videos is usually in Helvetica, but not always. How do you decide when to put something in a different typeface?

      the advantage of keeping it all the same, is you tend to see through the font and see the meaning without even seeing the font. but then again, after keeping it the same for a long time, it becomes powerful to use a different one occasionally

11.28.24  9:39 am   During presentations (like public speaking) I could have prepared so well like have everything planned out. But no matter how well I prepare I always black out and rattle on and on and say whatever comes to mind. And at the end I dont remember anything I said or if I made the point that I wanted to make. And then the feedback is usually quite positive. But still it would be nice to not feel like someone else takes control of my mind and body while im speaking because its just bound to go horribly wrong at some point right

      make it a fun game of discovery, discovering together with the audience what the prepared notes were. you and your audience will both will be equally surprised at which things resonate and which things don't
